HEADWORD: Cordaites
<hw>Cordaites</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a genus of tall Paleozoic trees
superficially resembling modern screw pines; they were structurally
intermediate in some ways between cycads and conifers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Cordaites</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

